"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5193363-2024-01-10-usa-basketball-player-pools-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"NBA PARIS - This is preposterous, to the point of non-belief, but on Wednesday a French reporter asked theBrooklyn Nets'Mikal Bridgesabout his hopes and/or intentions to play for Team USA at the Paris Olympics this summer, and he said he'd forgotten the Games were going to be here.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 90, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9596709558791607, \"rank\": 0.021444519958389623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 182, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999960105015, \"rank\": 3.9892185808637584e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the point\", \"from\": 37, \"to\": 46}, {\"ngram\": \"non\", \"from\": 50, \"to\": 53}, {\"ngram\": \"belief\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 60}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 78}, {\"ngram\": \"theBrooklyn Nets'Mikal\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 125}, {\"ngram\": \"his hopes\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 148}, {\"ngram\": \"intentions\", \"from\": 156, \"to\": 166}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 209}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bridges was seated before a throng of mostly French reporters Wednesday after the Nets practiced in a Parisian suburb, ahead of their Thursday game with theCleveland Cavaliers.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9596709558791607, \"rank\": 0.021444519958389623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bridges\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 294}, {\"ngram\": \"a throng\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 321}, {\"ngram\": \"the Nets\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"a Parisian suburb\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"their Thursday game\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 434}, {\"ngram\": \"theCleveland Cavaliers\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 462}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement TheNBAcoming to Paris is a big deal (Thursday's tilt will be the third regular-season game in France ever), and the upcoming Paris Games, in which the biggest stars in the NBA are expected to play for their countries, is a huge ancillary topic of discussion this week.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 496, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9493221527769361, \"rank\": 0.053343324534248934, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0659773444453446e-25, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"TheNBAcoming\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 491}, {\"ngram\": \"a big deal\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 514}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday's tilt\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"the third regular-season game\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"the upcoming Paris Games\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 615}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest stars\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"their countries\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge ancillary topic\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"discussion\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 736}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American players have been talking about Paris since the moment USA beat France in the Tokyo Olympic finals, and Bridges, a member of last summer's World Cup team that qualified the United States for the 2024 Olympics, surely had not forgotten.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 791, \"end\": 796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9493221527769361, \"rank\": 0.053343324534248934, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999942838258, \"rank\": 4.392417636954866e-09, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympic finals\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 857}, {\"ngram\": \"Bridges\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 880}, {\"ngram\": \"last summer's World Cup team\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 912}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the kind of deflection a player might use to get away from a line of questioning he does not want to answer - like he knows something that is not supposed to be out there yet.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1008}, {\"ngram\": \"deflection\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"a player\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"a line\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Just waiting to see - if (the invite) comes, it comes,\\\" Bridges toldThe Athletic, after the larger scrum.\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"if (the invite\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"Bridges toldThe Athletic\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"the larger scrum\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think I bear my head on it too much, because I am so locked in on trying to figure out everything here (with the Nets).\\\"\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my head\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"the Nets\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Frankly, it was a much more plausible answer, and in truth, according to Bridges and numerous league sources, Team USA has not sent any formal invites for its 12-man roster for Paris.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999960105015, \"rank\": 3.9892185808637584e-09, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999909546204, \"rank\": 9.045503510657307e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a much more plausible answer\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"truth\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1474}, {\"ngram\": \"Bridges\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous league sources\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"any formal invites\", \"from\": 1548, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"its 12-man roster\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1588}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, those sources said, USA Basketball will begin reaching out to potential prospects before January is out, running through between 35 and 40 names on a master list of players who primarily are Olympic or World Cup vets, many (but not all of them) stars, with room potentially for a few players who perhaps do not check any of those boxes.\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1626, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9682222333811579, \"rank\": 0.032820736317672086, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those sources\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"potential prospects\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"between 35 and 40 names\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"a master list\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic or World Cup vets\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1822}, {\"ngram\": \"room\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"a few players\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"those boxes\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least a few of the names on that list, the sources said, will be players from the 2023 World Cup team that finished fourth last summer, and the list is expected to be announced in the coming days or weeks.\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 2152, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the names\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"that list\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"the sources\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2019}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2023 World Cup team\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"the coming days\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"weeks\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Previously, USA managing director Grant Hill and coach Steve Kerr had suggested \\\"player pools\\\" would be discontinued; that, in the modern era, it was more effective for the American national team to send invites privately, rather than ask a larger group of players to try out.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1751283763131969e-26, \"text\": \"Grant Hill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Kerr\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\"}, {\"begin\": 2327, \"end\": 2349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998979637946, \"rank\": 1.0200169845813436e-07, \"text\": \"American national team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"player pools\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern era\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2295}, {\"ngram\": \"invites\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2365}, {\"ngram\": \"a larger group\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"players\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, USA Basketball pieced together the World Cup roster without a pool, and it was widely expected the same process would be followed for theOlympics.\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2445, \"end\": 2459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9682222333811579, \"rank\": 0.032820736317672086, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2443}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Cup roster\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"a pool\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"the same process\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2556}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's basketball, however, will continue using the player-pool system for 2024.\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2673, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women's basketball\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the player-pool system\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement But the interest in the 2024 Games is perhaps unprecedented, with young, upcoming stars like Bridges,Tyrese HaliburtonandAnthony Edwards, as well as aging superstars with gold medals likeLeBron JamesandKevin Durant, all hoping to play for Team USA.Steph Curry, who has two World Cup golds but has never played in the Olympics, has said he wants to play.Jayson TatumandDevin Booker, members of the Tokyo Games gold-medalist team, want to play.\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2898, \"end\": 2904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6950495277153082e-15, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the interest\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2705}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Games\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"young, upcoming stars\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2776}, {\"ngram\": \"Bridges\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2789}, {\"ngram\": \"Tyrese HaliburtonandAnthony Edwards\", \"from\": 2790, \"to\": 2825}, {\"ngram\": \"aging superstars\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2854}, {\"ngram\": \"Team USA.Steph Curry\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2948}, {\"ngram\": \"two World Cup golds\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2977}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3014}, {\"ngram\": \"Jayson TatumandDevin Booker\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 3071, \"to\": 3078}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games gold-medalist team\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So doesJoel Embiid, the reigning NBA MVP who has American and French passports and said he would play for the USA this summer.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3166, \"end\": 3173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.1060372625593153e-12, \"text\": \"NBA MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3195, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9596709558791607, \"rank\": 0.021444519958389623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3243, \"end\": 3246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"So doesJoel Embiid\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Creating a pool, or master list, or larger group of \\\"finalists\\\" allows the USA staff to keep a larger number of talented, perhaps deserving players engaged rather than discouraged, after the public declarations of interest from the biggest American stars.\", \"from\": 3261, \"to\": 3516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3336, \"end\": 3339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.8825716579522154, \"rank\": 0.13255401508525289, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3501, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9882295983209153, \"rank\": 0.006934136382745911, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Sta